        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 6:13AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 612 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairfield Bay, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parma...                          Austin in Conway County...
Fairfield Bay Marina...           Brownsville...
Scotland...                       Claude...
Formosa...                        Catholic Point...
Narrows Marina...                 Center Ridge...
Shirley...                        Brewer...
Choctow Recreation Area...        Woodrow...
Edgemont...                       Beverage Town...
Prim...                           Southside in Van Buren County...
Bee Branch...                     Whipple...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for central and
north central Arkansas.</instruction>
